1558042.title: 1049 Park Avenue - East 86th Street
1558042.folder: 1049 Park Avenue - East 86th Street, Manhattan, NY

722362f-a.text:
Park Avenue, east side, from 87th to 86th Streets, showing No. 1049 Park Avenue, an apartment house about four years old. The old 3-story frame No. 1047 together with the small builcings to the corner of 86th Street, is shortly to be demolished. Compure
picture taken from 86th Street early in 1924.
1922.
John Wallace Gillier, Photographer.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

722361f.text:

722359f-a.text:
1040 Park Avenue, at N. W. corner of 86th Street, newly
completed.
1924.

722360f-a.text:
1045 Park Avenue, at N. E. corner of 86th Street, showing a new apartment house replacing three four-story houses and one old 3-story frame house, Nos. 1041-47 inclusive. Compare with view taken from 67th Street in 1922.
On 86th Street may be seen the 86th Street Temple (Synagogue).  Notice the little gate leading into the park.  This is the exit from the old 86th Street station of the New York & Harlem Railway.
Early 1924.

Capitol Photographic Service.
Gift of R.M. Jenks.
